      <section eId="sec_CC-585">
        <num>CC 585</num>
        <heading>585.  Extraordinary charges</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 585.  Extraordinary charges.
The usufructuary is bound to pay the extraordinary charges that may be imposed, during the existence of the usufruct, on the property subject to it.  If these charges are of a nature to augment the value of the property subject to the usufruct, the naked owner shall reimburse the usufructuary at the end of the usufruct only for the capital expended.</p>
        </content>
